InventoryID: 45 Paestum, from C. Licinella (1968)—sporadic, environs of T. 6Non Sepcified8
Imagery Description: Dionysiac scene—the upper level seems to have been divided up as on the "loggia" scenes on Madrid 11094 and Paestum 20202 (nos. 127 and 134); in the first compartment is the bust of a woman, who held a thyrsus with a red fillet; below is part of a satyr with a thyrsus and a small part of another figure, who held a thyrsus with a fillet tied round it.
